{
  "_doc": "Curated 2D wireframe sketches for offline-trained inference.  Each entry is `(nodes, edges)` in raw pixel space (0..w, 0..h) — the same coordinate system that `_opencv_canny_fallback` returns. In production this would be a much larger corpus (image + topology pairs) stored in HDF5 or a parquet-backed bucket; the JSON mirror is deliberate so devs can diff-patch new samples without binary handlers. Schema versions below 1.0 are reserved for the legacy raw-pixel-image format.\n\nPer-sample `expected_nodes` / `expected_edges` fields (added on schema v1):\n  These document the AUTHORED topology — i.e., what `len(nodes)` / `len(edges)`   SHOULD be for this shape when drawn cleanly. They are passed-through metadata:   `_validate_sample` does not require or consume them, and `parse_wireframe_topology`   treats them as opaque. They equal `len(nodes)` / `len(edges)` by construction for   every authored sample, but the runtime cleaner (`_run_trained_topology` -> `_cleanup_topology`) may produce a final topology that matches expected_* exactly   (when all polyline segments exceed `priors['min_line_segment_px']=6.0`) or differs   slightly (a small handful of inner-spiral / tight-curve edges have chord < 6.0   and will be discarded; see the audit log printed by `tests/_tmp_build_samples.py`   for the exact count). The 32 samples added under schema v1 carry these fields;   the 8 original samples drawn before the metadata extension do not. Both groups   load and validate identically.\n\nSample categories (40 total):\n  - Polylines (8 original): square / triangle / line-pair / zigzag / pentagon /\n    L-wall / stairs / T-junction\n  - Curved strokes (10): semi-circle / shallow-arc / S-curve / J-curve /\n    C-clamp / hairpin-bend / sine-wave / fish-hook / spiral-coil /\n    roller-coaster-loop\n  - Multi-branch junctions (11): Y / X-cross / K / arrow-head / H-shape /\n    double-Y-bar / 5-arm-star / 6-arm-asterisk / trident / 2-level binary\n    tree / 3-level complete binary tree\n  - Isometric projections (11): cube-wireframe / open-top-box / pyramid /\n    octahedron / ramp / diamond / hex-plane / grid-plane / 3-step-stairs /\n    L-block / table-top\n",
  "schema_version": 1,
